{
  "text": "Then the adept, in becoming familiar with the Logos's archetype in each case, would then be able to most efficiently use the Logos's plan for evolution. Is this correct? I am Ra. In the archetypical mind one has the resource of not specifically a plan for evolution but rather a blueprint or architecture of the nature of evolution. This may seem to be a small distinction, but it has significance in perceiving more clearly the use of this resource of the deep mind.",
